He cut off his wings and tail as they were, opened their feathers and flattened them, flayed the rest of his skin, separated it into two pieces, tied one of them on his back and the other on his navel and under it, attached the tail behind him, and attached the wings to his biceps, which gave him cover, warmth and prestige among all the beasts so that they did not dispute or oppose him.
We thought that we would give them a glimpse of the secret of secrets in order to attract them to the side of the investigation and then repel them from that path, and we did not, however, leave what we have deposited in these few papers of secrets from a thin veil and a gentle curtain that is quickly violated for those who deserve it and condensed for those who do not deserve to exceed it so as not to exceed it.
He went back to Salaman and his companions and apologized for what he had spoken to him and disowned him. He informed them that he had seen the same opinion as them and was guided by the same path as them, and recommended them to stick to what they were doing in terms of adhering to the limits of the Shari'ah and the apparent deeds, not to delve into what does not concern them, to believe and accept the similarities, to reject innovations and whims and to follow the example of the righteous predecessors and abandon the novelties of the things.
He ordered them to avoid the practice of the common people of neglecting the Shari'ah and focusing on the world, and warned them against it with the utmost caution.
He and his companion, Absal, knew that this sought-after sect could not be saved except by this path, and that if they were removed from it to the realms of clairvoyance, they would not be able to join the ranks of the happy ones, and would wobble, relapse, and have a bad outcome.
If she continues in what she is until she reaches certainty, she will gain security and will be from the Companions of the Right, and as for the former, those are the close ones.
They said goodbye to them, separated from them, and were kind enough to return to their island until Allah, the Almighty, made it easy for them to cross to it.
Hayy ibn Yaqzan sought his honorable place in the manner in which he first sought it until he returned to it, and Absal followed his example until he came close to it, and they worshipped Allah in that island until they came to certainty.
This is the story of Hayy ibn Yaqzaan, Absal and Salman, which contains a piece of speech that is not found in a book or heard in the usual discourse, and it is from the hidden knowledge that only people who know Allah accept it and only people who are unaware of it are unaware of it.
We did not follow the path of the righteous Salaf in caring for it and being greedy for it.
However, what has made it easier for us to reveal this secret and pierce the veil is the corrupt opinions that have emerged in our time from the philosophers of the age, and they have declared them until they spread in the countries and their harm is widespread, and we feared that the weak people who rejected the imitation of the prophets - may Allah bless them - and wanted to imitate the fools and idiots would think that these opinions are the secrets that are confided to others and thus increase their love and fondness for them.
I ask my brothers who read this speech to accept my excuse for my leniency in explaining and tolerance in fixing it, for I did not do so except because I climbed to heights that are difficult to see, and I wanted to minimize the speech in a way that encourages people to enter the path.
I ask Allah for forgiveness and pardon, and that He may grant us knowledge of Him in the purest form, as He is gracious and merciful.
May peace be upon you, my brother, and may God's mercy and blessings be upon you.
